Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine light brown. Circular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 28a, 5 or 201, 22. Name Moschion.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0498)
